  <thing id="fRvnAlcHom" name="Alchemical Homunculus" description="By instilling a vat bubbling with alchemical mixtures with a portion of her own vital essences, the alchemist creates an alchemical homunculus, a grotesque and stunted, but largely harmless. form of life.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, lnt 13+.\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 25; 10 days; pint of alchemist&apos;s blood; 25 XP; 140 gp.  A character with this feat does not need to follow the construction rules given in the {i}Monster Manual{/i}.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} An alchemical homunculus uses the statistics and abilities provided in the {i}Monster Manual{/i}, but also gains acid resistance 10 and is affected by alchemical formulas as a living creature.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The DM should roll 1d4 on Table 4&#151;1 to select a flaw." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - create a homunculous" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Alch1Perm"/>
    <eval phase="First">perform forward[User.Alch1Perm]</eval>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnAncLeg" name="Ancestral Legacy" description="A mysterious relative or messenger has appeared and bestowed on you a valuable heirloom. Though you may not yet know its full significance, this birthright comes with a legacy of honor, power, and perhaps unspeakable sins.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You receive a free item. The DM must choose an item with a gold piece value equal to or less than one eighth of your starting wealth. If you take this feat at a level other than 1st level, the DM should consult Table 2-24 in the {i}Dungeon Master&apos;s Guide{/i} to determine your starting wealth. This item can be a weapon, armor, tool, art object, vehicle, animal, or even land (see Table 5-6 in the {i}DMG{/i}). The item always carries an Embarrassing curse that affects only you and your blood relatives. This item can be magical, but if so its curse is Frustrating rather than Embarassing.\n\nIn addition to the curse, whenever the item is worn, carried, or otherwise visible, it may give you a +2 bonus or -2 penalty to Charisma checks and Charisma-based skill checks. Whether this bonus or penalty applies depends on your audience, the nature of the item, and the reputation of your family. For example, a dagger your grandfather used to murder a rival could give a +2 bonus to checks with a scheming uncle, a -2 penalty to checks with a rival family&apos;s patriarch. It might also add a bonus or penalty to checks with serfs working your family&apos;s lands, depending on whether they viewed your family as a clan of firm guardians or murderous tyrants.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You may not take this feat more than once." compset="Feat" summary="Get an item linked to your family&apos;s past" uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="hName1" value="+2"/>
    <fieldval field="hName2" value="-2"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fShowWhat" tag="Freeform"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="9001"><![CDATA[if (field[hIsOn1].value <> 0) then
 foreach pick in hero from BaseSkill
  if (eachpick.islinkage[skillattr] <> 0) then
   if (eachpick.linkage[skillattr].tagis[thingid.aCHA] <> 0) then
    eachpick.field[Bonus].value += 1
   endif
  endif
 nexteach
elseif (field[hIsOn2].value <> 0) then
 foreach pick in hero from BaseSkill
  if (eachpick.islinkage[skillattr] <> 0) then
   if (eachpick.linkage[skillattr].tagis[thingid.aCHA] <> 0) then
    eachpick.field[Bonus].value -= 2
   endif
  endif
 nexteach
endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnCorPur" name="Corporeal Purgative" description="This purgative targets physical corruption caused by diseases, including supematural diseases such as mummy rot, and parasites, such as green slime and rot grubs. A secondary subject, of course,  risks contracting all that once ailed the now-healthy primary subject.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Emotional Purgative, Int 15+.\n\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 29; 1 day; 550 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} A primary subject must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 15 + alchemist&#146;s Intelligence modifier) or regurgitate the purgative, now infused with all of the subject&#146;s diseases and parasites.  A secondary subject must succeed at a Fortitude save (with the DC determined by the ailment) or contract all diseases present as if exposed to their original source.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} If the diseases are not transferred to a secondary subject before the purgative becomes inert, the impure energies return to their original host; the primary subject contracts all imbued ailments again." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - drink it and be cured of parasites and disease" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="User" tag="Alch2Perm"/>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Emotional Purgative required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnEmoPur] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 15 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnCorPrf" name="Corporeal Purifier" description="This soothing salve promotes the regeneration ofdamaged tissue in living creatures, noticeably reducing scar tissue.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, lnt 13+.\n\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 25; 24 hours; 140 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} Each application of this salve reduces OR [Outcast Rating] modifiers caused by scarring (such as the effects of goblyn feasting) by -1, to a minimum of 0.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The effects are temporary.  After a number of days equal to the Alchemy check, the scars quickly and painfully reform, along with their attendant OR [Outcast Rating] modifiers.  To make matters worse, the scars return in more extreme form, increasing the subject&apos;s OR modifier by +1." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - reduce a scarring OR penalty for a time" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnEmoPur" name="Emotional Purgative" description="The alchemist must specify a single emotion when brewing this purgative, working its alchemical criteria into the final solution.  A primary subject that regurgitates this purgative is rendered incapable of feeling this emotion for about half an hour.  A secondary subject is affected by the imbued emotion for a few minutes. While emotional purgatives may well have some insidious uses, they are extremely useful for investigators battling their own terror.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Int 13+.\n\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 25; 24 hours; 140 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} Use the {i}emotion{/i} spell for example emotions this formula can affect.  A primary subject must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 13 + alchemist&#146;s Intelligence modifier) or regurgitate the substance, now infused with the specified emotion.  The primary subject is rendered incapable of feeling this emotion for a number of minutes equal to the creator&#146;s Alchemy check.\n\nA secondary subject must succeed at a Fortitude save (at the DC above) or be overwhelmed by the imbued emotion (as if affected by the emotion spell) for a number of rounds equal to the Alchemy check.\n\n{i}Example:{/i} An alchemist creates a dose of fear purgative, rolling a 30 on the Alchemy check. A primary subject is rendered immune to fear effects for 30 minutes. A secondary subject is subject to the &#147;fear&#148; version of the emotion spell for 30 rounds.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The purgative targets the wrong emotion.  Roll 1d6 to select a random version of the {i}emotion{/i} spell.\n\n{b}\nd6      Emotion         Effect{/b}\n1        Despair          -2 morale pen saves, attack, ability checks, skill checks and damage rolls.\n2        Fear                 Flee in terror, (horror save?)\n3        Friendship     React more posiviely.  Shift attitude 1 step more favorable to you.\n4        Hate                React less favorably.   Shift attitude 1 step less favorable to you.\n5        Hope               +2 morale bon on saves, attack, ability &amp; skill checks, and damage rolls.\n6        Rage              +2 morale str &amp; con, +1 Will, -1 pen AC.  Compelled to fight, cannot flee or withdraw" compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - drink it and be cured of that emotion for a time" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>http://www.dandwiki.com/wiki/SRD3e:Emotion</comment>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnEmoChi" name="Enlightened Child" description="This formula creates an advanced form of the philosophical child. No longer satisfied with the mere creation of life, the alchemist who masrers this formula seeks to improve upon that which nature has created. The creatures spawned in these experiments are more powerful than philosophical children, but no less unnatural, and no less dedicated to their hubristic masters.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Alchemical Homunculus, Philosophical Child, Int 17+.\n\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 33; 40+ days; pint of alchemist&#146;s blood; tissue sample from base creature; 1,000 XP; 4,000+ gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} To create an {i}enlightened child{/i}, apply the &#147;Enlightened Child&quot; template to the base creature selected by the alchemist.  Unlike a {i}clone{/i}, the child possesses its own animating force.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} See Table 4-1.\n\n{b}Note:{/b} According to he sourcebook {i}Van Ritchen&apos;s Arsenal, Vol. 1{/i}, the template is called &quot;Alchemical Child,&quot; and is used for both Philosophical Child and Enlightened Child with minor alterations.  Because of Hero Lab&apos;s Mechanics.  They have been seperated into two Seperate Templates.  They cannot be used both at the same time." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - creates and advanced form of the philosophical child (see description)" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 17 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 17]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Alchemical Homunculus required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnAlcHom] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Philosophical Child required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnPhiChi] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnHexbre" name="Hexbreaker" description="You are skilled at unweaving the blasphemous fabric of the black arts. Evil magic seems to unravel particularly easily under your deft hands.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Non-evil alignment, Skill Focus (Spellcraft), Spellcaster level 5th\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You receive a +2 insight bonus to Spellcraft checks to identify a spell being cast if the spell in question requires a powers check. You receive a +2 bonus to your dispel check when you use {i}dispel magic{/i} against a spell that requires a powers check, regardless of whether it is a targeted dispel, an area dispel, or a counterspell." compset="Feat" summary="Skilled at dispelling dark magic" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Non-evil alignment required.">hero.tagis[Alignment.Evil] = 0</exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Skill Focus (Spellcraft) required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[kSpellcr].tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <prereq message="Caster 5th level required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[foreach pick in hero from BaseClHelp
 validif (eachpick.field[cCasterLev].value >= 5)
nexteach]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnEssCoa" name="Essential Coagulant" description="The alchemist drains the fading life force from either a dying subject or one recently dead.  The resulting coagulant contains the deceased subject&apos;s spirit, in its entirety.  This coagulant can then be injected into any living, corporeal creature.  The transplanted spirit takes root in its new host as if it had been reincarnated into that form.  Together with the creation of alchemical life, many alchemical philosophers view this dreadful formula as the key to immortality.  In truth, it is straying from the true path, a collapse into unnatural, artificial life.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Memory Coagulant, Purity [Innocence] Coagulant, Int 17+.\n\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 33; 1 day; 1,200 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} This coagulant can be drawn only from a subject that is either dying (below 0 hit points) or has been dead for no longer than a number of rounds equal to the Alchemy check.\n\nOnce the spirit is transferred, if the new host body has its own spirit (as all natural living creatures do), the transplanted soul manifests as an altemate personality.  Use the &#147;Multiple Personalities&quot; Madness effect in the {i}Ravenloft Setting{/i} book to determine when the soul can gain control of its host. If the host body has no mind or spirit of its own (as with an alchemical creation), the transplanted spirit gains full control of its new body.  Unlike {i}raise dead{/i} or similar magic, the deceased spirit is trapped by the coagulant and need not be willing to retum to a living body.\n\nThe soul can also be transferred to a fresh corpse, provided the body is completely intact and has been dead for no more than the Alchemy check in rounds.  lf the corpse meets these requirements, the infusion of a new life force restores the body to life.  Otherwise, the infused corpse animates as a type of corporeal undead with HD equal to half of the transferred spirit&#145;s level.\n\nSome life essence is always dispersed during the transferal. The transplanted spirit automatically loses 1 level, or 1 point of Constitution if the subject had only 1 Hit Die. If the spirit is not transplanted into a new host by the time the coagulant becomes inert, it is freed to move on to its final destination in the afterlife. While the spirit is trapped within the coagilant, however, spells such as {i}raise dead{/i} or {i}resurrection{/i} have no effect.\n\nCrafting or using essential coagulant requires a powers check.\n\n{i}Partial Failure:{/i} The transplanted soul is improperly anchored in its new host.  After a number of days equal to the Alchemy check, the subject receives one negative level per week.  If the subject drops to 0 HD, its spirit drains away entirely and the body dies." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - drink it and becomes infuse with a spirit (see description)" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 17 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 17]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Memory Coagulant required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnMemCoa] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Purity [Innocence] Coagulant required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnInnCoa] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnHolPur" name="Holistic Purifier" description="{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Corporeal Purifier, Philosophical Purifier, lnt 17+.\n\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 33; 1 day; 1,200 gp.\n\nAs with the philosophical purifier, the alchemist must select specific ethical and moral traits to infuse into the application at the time of creation.  Any living creature that ingests or is injected with this purifier undergoes a startling physical and mental transformation, its mind and body shifting to perfectly reflect the infused traits.\n\nWhen the transformation ends, all subconscious elements of the imbued alignment are purged from the subject&apos;s psyche, and the subject remains remarkably true to his core philosophies for quite some time.  While a few alchemists in the past have relied on this formula as a tool to resist base temptations, even they knew that they had sacrificed true enlightenment for an ultimately destructive substitute.\n\n{i}Editor&apos;s Note: This knowledge recently aided Laurie and I in the resolution of a series of murders taking place in Morfenzi.  The murders greatly benefited a highly respected merchent, but several of the crims had been witnessed by folk who discribed a degenerate thug, perhaps even a caliban, who bore little resemblance to the suspect.  Indeed, the killer had done little to conceal his identity.  Armed with our new knowlwedge, however we searched the merchant&apos;s home and discovered a small cache of purifiers that he had somehow accuired.  We suspect that he had been transforming himself into his own hired killer, presumably so as to keep both his hands and soul free of stain as he eliminated his rivals.  Unfortunately, the Falkovian authorities executed the man immediately once we brought our findings to light, preventing us from truely confirming his guilt.{/i} &#151;GWF\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} The physical transformation is as effective as the {i}alter self{/i} spell; like that spell, the physical changes induced by this formula grant a + 10 bonus to the subject&#146;s Disguise checks.  Creatures that become chaotic may develop asymmetrical features, while creatures that become evil may appear markedly degenerate. Creatures that become good may grow more beatific, while those that become lawful may look perfectly symmetrical. For each step the subject&#146;s moral alignment shifts toward good, its OR lowers by an effective -1, while the reverse is true for subjects that become evil. (Thus, the OR of a good creature that becomes evil rises by +2 for the transformation&#146;s duration.)\n\nWhile transformed, the subject&#146;s behavior is always perfectly true to the infused alignment. The transformation&apos;s duration is equal to twice the Alchemy check in minutes.\n\nFor a number of days following the transfonnation equal to the Alchemy check, the purifier&apos;s aftereffects grant the subject a competence bonus to Will saves to resist any mind-influencing effects that would cause her to act against her alignment. The bonus is +1 for each step the subject&#145;s alignment changed while transformed, to a maximum of +4 (as with a lawful good creature that had become chaotic evil).\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The purifier functions normally but is addictive.  When the purifier&apos;s after effects wear off, the subject passes through a detoxifying period, suffering an effective reduction of &#151;2 points from each ability score for a number of days equal to the Alchemy score.  lf the subject acquires another dose of the purifier, she must succeed at a Will save (DC 17 + Intelligence modifier of the alchemist who created the addictive purifier) to resist using the new dose.  Taking another dose of the same alignment purifier immediately removes all detoxification penalties." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - like the alter self spell (see description)" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 17 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 17]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Corporeal Purifier required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnCorPrf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Philosophical Purifier required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnPhiPur] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnIndomi" name="Indomitable" description="You have an exceptional mind that bounces back from numbing terror with confidence and determination. Though encounters with super-natural horrors might shatter your world and haunt your dreams, you are firmly resolved to destroy such creatures.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: WIS 11\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Whenever you fail a Horror or Madness save prompted by a creature&apos;s presence or actions, you thereafter receive a +1 morale bonus to your attack rolls and Gather Information, Knowledge, and Sense Motive checks when you are pursuing that creature&apos;s destruction. If you fail multiple Horror or Madness saves, the effects of this feat are not cumulative.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You must have suffered a moderate or major Horror or Madness effect." compset="Feat" summary="Get morale bonus, attack bonus and Gather Information, Knowledge and Sense Motive  bonus on creature that made you fail an Horror or Madness check" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Wisdom 11 required."><![CDATA[child[aWIS].field[aFinalVal].value >= 11]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnInnCoa" name="Innocence Coagulant" description="The alchemist drains the lingering spiritual purity from the corpse of a creature that died while still uniainred by sin.  If this coagulant is then injected into a creature corrupted by spiritual impurity, the coagulated innocence bums like acid.  If the creature has not fallen to evil, the lingering purity temporarily bolsters the subject&apos;s spiritual defenses.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Memory Coagulant, Int 15+.\n\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 29; 1 day; 550 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} The alchemist must drain the fresh corpse of a humanoid that died Innocent to create this coagulant.  A fell creature injected with coagulated innocence suffers damage, as determined by the depth of the creatures evil taint (see Table 4-2). In addition, coagulated innocence is considered blessed, which means it has special effects on certain creatures.\n{b}\nTable 4-2: Coagulated Innocence Effects\nDamage Target&#146;s Condition{/b}\n\n1d6         Creature has failed 1 powers check or is afflicted by an embarrassing curse\n2db         Creature has failed 2 powers checks or is afflicted by a frustrating curse\n3d6         Creature has failed 3 powers checks or is afflicted by a troublesome curse\n4d6         Creature has failed 4 powers checks or is afflicted by a dangerous curse (including lycanthropy)\n5d6         Creature has failed 5 powers checks or is afflicted by a lethal curse (including uncleath)\n6d6         Darklord or outsider with &#147;Evil&#148; descriptor\n\nIf a good-aligned creature that does not fall into any of the conditions above is injected with the coagulated purity, she must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 15 + alchemist&#146;s Int modifier, harmless) or gain the benefits applied by Innocence for a number of rounds equal to half the Alchemy check.  The Innocent corpse to be harvested must have been dead for no more than the Alchemy check in days, and any given corpse can be drained of its lingering Innocence only once.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} Most of the collected Innocence dissipates.  The thinned coagulant has no effect on good subjects and inflicts damage to corrupted creatures in increments of only 1d3 points rather than 1d6." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - cause damage to evil tainted creatures" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 15 required"><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Memory Coagulant required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnMemCoa] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnLogMnd" name="Logical Mind" description="Though the Realm of Dread might be steeped in the supernatural, you put your faith in rationality and observation. When faced with the unbelievable, this scholarly skepticism is a source of mental fortitude.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Int 15, 1 rank in at least one Knowledge skill (choose from architecture and engineering, geography, history, nature or nobility and royalty), non-chaotic alignment.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You receive a +4 resistance bonus to Will saves against spells, spell-like effects, and supernatural effects, and to mundane Fear, Horror, and Madness saves prompted by creatures with spell-like or supernatural abilities.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: Once you take this feat, you can no longer purchase ranks in Lore skills or make Lore skill checks untrained. You may still attempt checks with Lore skills in which you already possess ranks." compset="Feat" summary="Resistance bonuses to Will checks" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Non-chaotic alignment required.">hero.tagis[Alignment.Chaotic] = 0</exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 15 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    <prereq message="1 rank in Knowledge (architecture and engineering, geography, history, nature or nobility and royalty) required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[foreach pick in hero from BaseSkill where "thingid.kKnowArcEn | thingid.kKnowGeog | thingid.kKnowHist | thingid.kKnowNat | thingid.kKnowNoble"

validif (eachpick.field[kUserRanks].value >= 1)

nexteach]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnMemCoa" name="Memory Coagulant" description="The alchemist drains the imprinted knowledge from a corpse.  If this coagulant is then injected into a living creature, that subject gains access to the deceased creature&apos;s memories for several minutes.  The congealed memories are hazy and indistinct, but by concentrating the subject can draw the answers to specific questions from the deceased subject&apos;s memories.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, lnt 13+.\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 25; 24 hours; 140 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} The living subject gains access to the deceased creature&#146;s memories for a duration equal to half the Alchemy check in minutes. The subject can recall the answers of up to (Alchemy check / 4) questions as if she were the deceased creature.  Any corpse that has had its memories drained cannot he spoken to with the spell speak with dead.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The subject is flooded with the emotions the deceased felt in the final few moments of its life.  If the corpse suffered a violent death, the subject may need to make a Fear or Horror save, as appropriate." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - get the memory of a deceased person" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnMuse" name="Muse" description="You possess the rare sort of beauty or spirit that feeds the divine flame of creativity. Your very presence inspires passion and stirs others to works or creative genius.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Cha 15\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When allies attempt a Perform check within thirty feet of you and you are within the allies&apos; line of sight, they receive a +2 circumstance bonus to their roll. This effect does not extend to any creatures other than your allies unles you wish it to. This is an extraordinary ability. You can grant a +2 circumstance bonus to an ally who is using a Craft sill to create an item, but you must spend all of the item&apos;s construction time in the company of the creator and your activities must otherwise be limited to talking, eating and resting. You receive a +2 bonus to Bluff, Diplomacy, Gather Information, and Perform checks when interacting with a character who has at least 8 ranks in Craft or Perform. Whenever you are reduced to below 0 hit points, any allies in your presence with a Charisma of 12 or higher must make a Horror save (DC 20).\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You may take this feat only at character creation." compset="Feat" summary="Help allies in their Perform or Craft checks" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Charisma 15 required."><![CDATA[child[aCHA].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnNinLiv" name="Nine Lives" description="You seem to be protected, perhaps by a guardian spirit, perhaps by a malign power that wants to keep you alive long enough to deal with you personally. Regardless, you have a penchant for survivng lethal situations.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: If you fail a Fortitude or Reflex save and are reduced to -10 hit points or below as a direct result, you may take two points of permanent Charisma drain to re-roll that saving throw. If you fail the re-roll, you can take another two points of Charisma drain to roll yet again, and so on. This is an extraordinary ability. The Charisma drain can be recovered as normal with {i}restoration{/i} or similar magic, but this ability can only be used a number of times in your character&apos;s life equal to her Charisma score at the time of character creation.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You may take this feat only at character creation." compset="Feat" summary="Trade charisma to reroll fatal checks" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnPhiChi" name="Philosophical Child" description="The alchemist concocts an advanced form of alchemical life &#151; one of the very constructs van Richten wamed of.  The alchemist must provide a measure of her own blood, symbolically donating a portion of her life force, and a tissue sample (blood, flesh, etc.) from a corporeal creature the alchemist wishes to recreate.  This creature must be alive when the tissue sample is taken, and it can be the alchemist himself; I have heard tales of alchemists who used this fomiula as a step toward obtaining an unnatural form of immortality. just as often, however, misguided alchemists use these creatures to create perfectly loyal servants.\n\nAfter twenty days of brewing, the &quot;child&quot; can be drawn from its vat as a viable creature in infant form.  If the alchemist wishes, she can artificially age the child by continuing to brew it for six hours per year she wishes it to age.  Thus, an alchemist who wants to create a physically-twenty-year-old &#147;child&#148; would brew the creation for a total of twenty-five days.  Each additional day of brewing consumes an additional 5 gp in raw materials.  Once drawn from its vat, however, the &quot;child&quot; solidifies and can no longer be aged by this method.\n\nA philosophical child is identical to the creature it is modeled on, at least to outward appearances, assuming that it is advanced to the same age and that the original creature possessed no distinguishing marks such as tattoos or scars.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Alchemical Homunculus, Int 15+\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 29; 20+ days; pint of alchemist&#146;s blood; tissue sample from base creature; 250 XP; 1,000+ gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} To create a philosophical child, apply the {i}&#147;Alchemical Child&quot;{/i} template (see below) to the base creature selected by the alchemist. Unlike a {i}clone{/i}, the child possesses its own animating force.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} See Table 4-1." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - create an &quot;Alchemical Child&quot; (see description)" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 15 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Alchemical Homunculus required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnAlcHom] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnPhiPur" name="Philosophical Purifier" description="The alchemist selects specific moral or ethical traits, infusing them into the concoction.  lf a living creature ingests or is injected with this purifier, its personality temporarily changes to reflect the chosen traits more strongly.  This purifier can bolster the user against evil enchantments, but it can also be used as a sinister form of mind control.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Corporeal Purifier, lnt 15+.\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 29; 1 day; 550 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} The alchemist must select a specific alignment (lawful good, neutral evil, etc.) to infuse into the application at the time of creation.  1d4 rounds after a subject is exposed to this purifier, it must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 15 + alchemist&#146;s intelligence modifier) or have its alignment shift by two steps along the moral and ethical axis toward the infused alignment.  {i}Example:{/i} A chaotic evil creature injected with &#147;purified lawful good&#148; might become lawful evil, true neutral, or chaotic good.\n\nThis temporary alignment change has a duration equal to the Alchemy check in minutes, and does not require a Madness save.  If the subject already has the infused alignment (such as a lawful neutral creature injected with &#147;purified lawful neutral&quot;), then it remains perfectly true to its alignment for the duration. Not even magical compulsion can force the affected creature to act against its alignment.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} lf the subject&apos;s alignment is not the same as the infused alignment, the involuntary alignment change does require a Madness save with a DC of (15 + the alchemist&apos;s Intelligence modifier)." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - infuse alignment" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 15 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Corporeal Purifier required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnCorPrf] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnPorten" name="Portents" description="You are blessed with hazy visions of the near future. These take the form of vague feelings of comfort or dread that manifest on the cusp of pivotal choices.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: WIS 15\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action, you can use {i}augury{/i} as the spell cast by a sorcerer of a level equal to your character level. This ability is usable once per day and requires no spell components. Once used, you cannot use this ability again until you have rested for at least 8 hours. This is a supernatural ability. It does not provoke attacks of opportunity, though like a spell it can be disrupted if you fail a Concentration check." compset="Feat" summary="Gain the use of {i}Augury{/i} 1/day." uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnQuinte" name="Quintessence" description="This quicksilver-like fluid is strongly imbued with positive energy.  Any living creature that ingests or is injected with quintessence immediately feels revived, and its body is inspired to heal its wounds.  Quintessence also burns the undead like acid, for their unclean bodies are empowered by the very antithesis of life.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Int 13+.\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 25; 24 hours; 140 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} The subject immediately heals 3d8 points of damage and any penalties imposed by fatigue are negated.  Any undead creature that ingests or is injected with quintessence suffers 3d8 points of damage (no saving throw).\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The weakened quintessence restores or inflicts only 2d6 points of damage, respectively." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - heal subject" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnRegSal" name="Regenerative Salve" description="A living creature can use this salve to reattach a severed limb by holding the body part in place for a few seconds while the energized flesh mends. The replacement limb can be the original or it can be harvested from a corpse, but the limb must not have been separated from a living host for more than one hour.  After this grace period, the limb degrades beyond use.  If the original limb is reattached, it recovers fully.  Limbs taken from the dead function normally but gradually take on a shriveled and discolored appearance.  Each application of this salve is sufficient to reattach one body part.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Quintessence, lnt 15+.\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 29; 1 day; 550 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} The severed limb must be held in place for one round.  A replacement limb collected from the dead uses its new host&#146;s Strength and Dexterity scores.  The limb&apos;s disfigurement increases the subject&apos;s OR by +1.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The effects are temporary.  After a number of days equal to the Alchemy check, the restored limb dies and becomes gangrenous.  The gangrenous limb inflicts 1d4 points of permanent Constitution drain each day until its host dies or the limb is amputated." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - attach new limbs" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 15 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 15]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Quintessence required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnQuinte] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnSceGra" name="Scent of the Grave" description="You carry an unholy stench that is undetectable to all creatures but animals. The beasts of the earth are frightened and intimidated by the sheer wrongness of your scent.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Animals suffer a -2 morale penalty to their attack rolls and skill checks when within 30 feet of you. For animals with the Scent special quality, this penalty rises to -4. You receive a +4 profane bonus to Intimidate checks with animals. You may never have an animal companion or cohort, and you suffer a -4 profane penalty to Handle Animal checks. You can have a familiar or Paladin&apos;s mount only if it is a dread companion. This is an extraordinaty ability.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: This feat often manifests following a close brush with lycanthropes or the undead, but some characters -- particularly calibans -- possess it from birth." compset="Feat" summary="Your unholy stench makes animal fear you." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnSmitte" name="Smitten" description="You are truly and deeply in love, in the purest storybook sense. Your love is not necessarily requited, but acts as a source of strength and purpose, for you would cross oceans and move mountains to protect your beloved.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Select a humanoid creature, or any creature that at least appears humanoid. That individual is your beloved. When your beloved is within your line of sight, you receive a +1 morale bonus to attack and saving throws. If your beloved is threatened by physical or magical harm, including mental attacks or control, this bonus rises to +2. If your beloved is reduced to 0 hit points or below in your presence, you must make a Horror save (DC 20). If your beloved dies or is revealed to be a supernatural creature (such as a lycanthrope or vampire), you must make a Madness save (DC 20).\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You cannot take this feat more than once, even if your beloved dies. This feat has no benefit after your beloved dies, and cannot be replaced with another feat." compset="Feat" summary="You are in love; get morale bonus check when beloved is present" uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="hName1" value="Beloved nearby"/>
    <fieldval field="hName2" value="Beloved endangered"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fShowWhat" tag="Freeform"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="10000"><![CDATA[if (field[hIsOn2].value <> 0) then
 hero.childfound[vFort].field[BonMorale].value += 2
 hero.childfound[vRef].field[BonMorale].value += 2
 hero.childfound[vWill].field[BonMorale].value += 2
 hero.childfound[Attack].field[BonMorale].value += 2
elseif (field[hIsOn1].value <> 0) then
 hero.childfound[vFort].field[BonMorale].value += 1
 hero.childfound[vRef].field[BonMorale].value += 1
 hero.childfound[vWill].field[BonMorale].value += 1
 hero.childfound[Attack].field[BonMorale].value += 1
endif]]></eval>
