  <thing id="fRvnSpiLig" name="Spirit of the Light" description="You are the candle in the darkness and the harbor in the storm. You have a soul that seems to put others at ease and give them strength in times of grief and terror.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: CHA 13, good alignment\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Your allies receive a +1 sacred bonus to Fear, Horror, and Madness saves to counteract sinkholes of evil as long as they remain within 30&apos; of you. When in your presence, a creature that has failed a Horror or Madness save receices a +2 sacred bonus to its recovery checks. You must spend at least eight hours a day with the creature each day following the failed save. Your activities during the eight hours do not matter, but you must remain within 60&apos; of that creature for the duration. This is an extraordinary ability.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You may takes this feat only at first level." compset="Feat" summary="Allies get bonus to Fear, Horro and Madness checks" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <exprreq message="Charisma 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aCHA].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Good alignment required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Alignment.Good] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnSpiPur" name="Spiritual Purgative" description="This purgative can rid a living creature of spiritual maladies, including enchanrments, possessing entities, and curses, including the dread disease of lycanthropy.  Curses are strangely unpredictable, however.  Some curses, no matter how seemingly minor, cannot be expelled from their host by any means, and all curses return to their Hue hosts unlex passed on to a secondary subject before the purgatjve loses its potency.\n\nIn short, a spiritual purgative can free a primary subject from many horrific ailments, but often only at the cost of passing this burden to the shoulders of some other unfortunate.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Emotional Purgative, Corporeal Purgative, Int 17+.\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 33, 1 day, 1,200 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} This purgative affects mind-influcncing spell effects, possessing entities (such as odems, ghosts with the malevolence special attack, or casters of the magic jar spell), and most curses. Spiritual purgatives cannot expel curses bestowed by failed powers checks, including the curse that binds a darklord to his domain. A primary subject must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 17 + alchemist&#146;s Intelligence modifier) or regurgitate the substance, now infused with all of the subject&apos;s spiritual maladies.\n\nlf a possessing entity is expelled, it immediately separates from the imbued purgative and is free to act as it wishes, including new attempts to possess the subject again, if possible. Enchantments and curses remain imbued in the purgative. If the imbued purgative is then passed to a secondary subject, the effects are transferred to that creature. The secondary subject is subject to the same saving throws to resist these maladies that the primary subject received (if any).\n\nIf an imbued curse is not transferred to a suitable secondary subject (one capable of being afflicted by that curse) within a certain time period (given below), the curse automatically reverts to the primary subject and is no longer imbued in the purgative.\n{b}\n  Curse                        Transferal\nSeverity                      Time Limit{/b}\nEmbarrassing    Alchemy check in hours\nFrustrating         Alchemy check x2 in minutes\nTroublesome     Alchemy check in minutes\nDangerous        Alchemy check x2 in rounds\nLethal               Alchemy check in round\n\nTransferring corruption to a secondary subject warrants a powers check.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} If the primary subject fails her Fortitude save, then the subject expels a portion of her own life force along with the spiritual corruption.  The subject receives 2 negative levels.  These negative levels can be dispelled by the standard methods." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat - expels mind-affecting spells, possessing entities (see description)" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 17 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 17]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Emotional Purgative required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnEmoPur] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Corporeal Purgative required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnCorPur] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnSwoEne" name="Sworn Enemy" description="You have pledged to destroy a specific breed of monster, such as aberrations or the undead. When you meet such creatures on the field of battle, your attacks are stoked by your hunter&apos;s fury.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Skill Focus (Knowledge [monster lore]). This Knowlegde skill must match your enemy creature type. You must have once been reduced to 0 hit points or below by a creature of your enemy type.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Select a creature type as your enemy: aberrations, animals, constructs, dragons, elementals, fey, giants, humanoids, magical beasts, oozes, outsiders, plants, undead, or vermin. You must select a subtype if your enemy is the humanoid type, but need not if it is the outsider type. You receive a +1 morale bonus to your attack rolls against that creature type, but only when you know you are facing such a creature. For example, if your enemy is humanoid (shapechanger), you do not receive the bonus when attacking a lycanthrope in humanoid form that you do not know to be a lycanthrope.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You cannot choose your own creature type unless you are evil. This feat cannot be taken more than once." compset="Feat" summary="Morale bonus when fighting a monster type" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fShowWhat" tag="Freeform"/>
    <prereq message="Skill Focus (Monster Lore) required.">
      <validate><![CDATA[foreach pick in hero from BaseSkill where "User.MonLore"
 validif (eachpick.tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0)
nexteach]]></validate>
      </prereq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnTisReg" name="Tissue Regenerator" description="This formula functions like an even more potent version of the {i}regenerative salve{/i}.  The lost body part is no longer needed.  Instead, the tissue regenerator so empowers the user&apos;s flesh that its grows a replacement part from the stump of the missing limb over the course of a few minutes.  Beware, however; although the new limb is indistinguishable from that which it replaced, it is not truly part of its host.  It is as much a form of alchemical life as a homunculus, arid if the formula is imperfect, the side effects can be severe.\n\n{b}Prerequisites:{/b} Brew Potion, Quintessence, Regenerative Salve, Int 17+\n{b}Formulation:{/b} DC 33; 1 day; 1,200 gp.\n\n{b}Effects:{/b} The new limb grows over the course of 2d10 rounds.  The regenerator also cures 5d4 points of damage.  The new limb is an alchemical construct but functions identically to the original limb it replaced.\n\n{b}Partial Failure:{/b} The DM should roll 1d3 on Table 4-3 to randomly select a flaw:\n\nTable 4-3: Flawed Alcemical limbs\nDie Roll    Imperfection\n1              The limb is grotesquely misshapen.  The |imb&apos;s Strength and Dexterity\n                 scores are each modified by +Id4&#151;2 (-1 to +2) points.  These modifiers\n                affect any action that relies on the new limb. The monstrous limb adds\n                +2 to the host&#146;s OR when visible.\n2              The limb is actually a dread golem with a dim consciousness of its own.  \n                lt may impulsively act on the host&apos;s subccnscious  desires, like a dread\n                companion. If the host tries to restrain or harm the limb, it may lash out\n                to defend itself or even attempt to murder its host.\n3              The limb has a drastically limited lifespan. After an initial number of days\n                equal to the Alchemy check, the limb loses 1 point  each from its Strength\n                and Dexterity scores each week.  When either score reaches 0, the limb\n                dissolves into ichor." compset="Feat" summary="Alchemical Feat -  Makes new limb grow (see description)" uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Alchemical"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Intelligence 17 required."><![CDATA[child[aINT].field[aFinalVal].value >= 17]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Brew Potion required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fBrewPot] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Quintessence required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnQuinte] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Regenerative Salve required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fRvnRegSal] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnUnseen" name="Unseen" description="Provided you remain perfectly still, you can hide in plain sight. Through some perplexing trick of the light or the mind, other creatures seem to simply overlook you.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Skill Focus (Bluff), Skill Focus (Hide)\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Whenever you are not being observed, you can conceal yourself as a free action, making yourself invisible as though affected by the spell {i}invisibility{/i}. You can take no actions while concealed, including moving or talking. The effect lasts as long as you take no actions. This is an extraordinary ability, though {i}see invisibility{/i}, {i}true sight{/i}, and similar spells will reveal your presence. In all other respects this ablity is treated as a glamer, and may be disbelieved." compset="Feat" summary="When unobserved, conceal yourself as a free action" uniqueness="useronce">
