    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Skill Focus (Bluff) required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[kBluff].tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Skill Focus (Hide) required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[kHide].tagis[Helper.SkillFocus] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fRvnWarGes" name="Warding Gesture" description="At some point in the past, a relative or friend taught you a simple folk gesture thought to keep minions or evil at bay. Though you rely on this superstition reflexively, unnatural creatures are genuinely fearful of you when you brandish such a sign. Whether this is because of its occulr power or simply your {i}belief{/i} in its power is uncertain.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: WIS 11, CHA 11\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Choose a creature type: aberrations, animals, constructs, dragons, elementals, fey, giants, humanoids, magical beasts, oozes, outsiders, plants, undead, or vermin. You need not select a subtype if you choose the outsider type. As a standard action that provokes an attack of opportunity, you can make a simple gesture. Treat the gesture as a passive gaze attack (see &quot;Gaze Attacks&quot; in the {i}DMG{/I}). Creatures of your chosen type must make a Fear save (DC = 10 + 1/2 your character level + your Charisma bonus) if they view the gesture. Creatures that make their Fear saves are immune to your gesture for 24 hours. You must have at least one hand free to make the gesture. You can make the gesture only once per encounter, but it is usable an unlimited number of times per day. This is an extraordinary ability.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You may take this feat multiple times. Each time you must designate a new creature type that is affected by the gesture." compset="Feat" summary="Make a warding gesture against a creature type">
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fShowWhat" tag="Freeform"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="21000"><![CDATA[var DC as number
DC = 10 + round(herofield[tHitDice].value/2,0,-1) + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value

field[livename].text = field[name].text & " (DC " & DC & ")"]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Charisma 11 required."><![CDATA[child[aCHA].field[aFinalVal].value >= 11]]></exprreq>
