  <thing id="sBrdInsaTh" name="Insatiable Thirst" description="The victim of this spell does anything within the limits of its alignment to consume any potable liquid it can ?nd while it is affected. Of course, the victim does not become an imbecile and will not knowingly drink harmful liquids such as poison or acid.  The victim is also allowed to take free actions like calling for help. If the only way for a victim to slake its thirst is to get past an opponent or other obstacle, it will resort to violence. A successful Concentration check (which can be attempted untrained) allows the victim to ignore its thirst long enough to perform more complex actions, such as casting a spell or attacking. The victim must make the check each round it wishes to ignore its thirst.\n\nAquatic creatures suffer a &#151;2 racial penalty to their saving throw." compset="Spell">
