  <thing id="ipRLDeBane" name="Death Bane" description="A death bane weapon has a +3 enhancement bonus and deals an extra 2d6 damage to the [specific] named individual.\n\nCrafting or using this item requires a powers check.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 11th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}summon monster l{/i}, {i}slay living{/i}, the true name of the individual the weapon is created to slay; {i}Market Price{/i}: +3 bonus\n\n{b}Source: {/b} {i}Van Richten&apos;s Arsenal Vol. 1{/i}" compset="ItemPower" summary="+3 Enh Bonus; and deals 2d6 to specific named individual.">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="3"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="CustomSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipRLFeyFor" name="Fey-Forged" description="Fey-Forged weapons bypass all damage reduction and weapon immunities of creatures of fey type.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 20th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}wish{/i}, wood and metal from the Shadow Rift; {i}Market Price{/i}: +4 bonus\n\n{b}Source: {/b} {i}Van Richten&apos;s Arsenal Vol. 1{/i}" compset="ItemPower" summary="Fully overcomes the damage reduction of the Fey type.">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="4"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipRLHeaSkr" name="Heartseeker" description="This enchantment can be applied to piercing weapons only.  With a successful critical hit, a {i}heartseeker{/i} weapon pierces the target&apos;s heart (if it has One).  Some creatures, such as plants and oozes, have no hearts.  Others, such as constructs and undead other than vampires, are unaffected.  Most other creatures are instantly killed when their heart is impaled.  However, outsiders may make a Fortitude save (DC 15) to survive and take standard damage.  A vampire stuck by a critical hit from a {i}heartseeker{/i} weapon of at least Small size is immobilized as if it had been staked, though the undead creature does not suffer double damage.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 12th; Prerequisites: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}slay living{/i}, ash wood, a vial of blood; {i}Market Price{/i}: +5 bonus\n\n{b}Source: {/b} {i}Van Richten&apos;s Arsenal Vol. 1{/i}" compset="ItemPower" summary="Impails heart on critical hit, killing instantly.  Immobilizes Vampires.">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="5"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="P"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Ranged"/>
    <tag group="PowerReq" tag="Thrown"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipRLProtec" name="Protection" description="These weapons gain a +2 enhancement bonus and deal an extra 1d4 damage when used to protect the subject of their enchantment.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 5th; {i}Prereqttisites{/i}: Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}greater magic weapon{/i}, symbol of the person, place, or thing to be protected; {i}Market Price{/i}: +2 bonus\n\n{b}Source: {/b} {i}Van Richten&apos;s Arsenal Vol. 1{/i}" compset="ItemPower" summary="{size 35}+2 Enh bon and +1d4 if used to protect speci named subject.">
    <fieldval field="iPrice" value="2"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="PowerType" tag="Weapon"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="CustomSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLAbbrDr" name="Abber Dream-Catcher" description="{i}Abber dream-catcher{/i} protects against all dream-influencing spells as well as the intrusions of such creatures as night hags, bastelli, and dream spawn. Any creature or effect blocked by the dream-catcher is blocked for the duration of the night.  Any Abber nomad may create one Abber dream-catcher per day (a process requiring eight hours), regardless of class or level, providing she possesses the necessary materials on hand (twigs, string, and beads). Abber dream-catcher cannot block dream invasions by darklords.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 7th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Create Wondrous Item, {i}dream{/i}, {i}nightmare{/i}, {i}protection from evil{/i}; {i}Market Price{/i}: 5,780 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: -" compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="5780"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="6"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="AlwaysAvl"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLAmBeaI" name="Amulet of the Beast, Ivory" description="{b}Flavor Text:{/b} This cursed amulet is an ivory disk on a chain.  It usually bears the image of a wild, lupine creature bound in chains.  Any person who dons the amulet aquires all of the symptoms of {i}afflicted lycanthropy{/i}.  Each amulet turns the wearer into a specific animal type, which is usually depicted on the disk.\n\nThe accursed wearer&#146;s creature type does not change to &#147;shapechanger&quot; and she does not carry the Dread Disease; she cannot infect other creatures with lycanthropy. The wearer cannot remove the amulet unless remove curse is successfully cast on it.\n\nRemoving the amulet also removes all symptoms of lycanthropy. Crafting this item requires a powers check.\n\n{i}Caster Level{i}: 7th; {i}Prerequisites{i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}bestow curse{/i}, {i}induce lycanthropy{/i}, pinch of fur from chosen lycanthrope type; {i}Market Price{/i}: 98,000 gp." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="98000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpNeck"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLAmBeS" name="Amulet of the Beast, Silver" description="Flavor Text:\nThis item is forged of silver but is otherwise identical to amulet above [{i}Amulet of the Beast, Ivory{/i}].  A lycanthrope wearing this amulet cannot transform into any of its alternate forms, even if exposed to its trigger.  The amulet does not prevent other forms of polymorphing or shapechanging howerever.  Should the unspeakable occur during a lycanthrope hunt, an amulet such as this can offer an afflicted victim relief from his curse.  The amulet can also prevent a natural lycanthrope from transforming, but in this case no magic force prevents the amulet&apos;s removal.\n\nThis item is identical to the {i}Amulet of the Beast, Ivory{/i} in all ways except that it is made out of silver and supresses the ability to shapeshift into their alternate forms.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 7th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}suppress lycanthropy{/i}, pinch of fur from any afflicted lycanthrope; {i}Market Price{/i}: 56,000 gp." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="56000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpNeck"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLBellWa" name="Bell of Warding" description="The tolling of the bell casts {i}imprisonment{/i} on all elementals, fey, outsiders, and undead within a half-mile radius. The {i}imprisonment{/i} lasts for one hour, at which time, unless the bell of warding is rung again to renew its enchantment, the imprisoned creatures are freed.  A bell of warding cannot imprison a darklord.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 20th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}bless{/i}, {i}imprisonment{/i}, 200 lb. of gold (10,000 gp), 1,300 lb. of iron (130 gp), 500 lb. of silver (25,000 sp); {i}Market Price{/i}: 61,130 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: 2,000 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="61130"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="2000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLBloodG" name="Blood-Seeker Garlic" description="Flavor Text:\nThis item is a bulb of garlic specially raised through watering with the blood of a vampire.  When thrown at a vampire, a bulb that strikes the beast quickly shoots out questing rootlets that burrow into the vampire&apos;s flesh, sucking up the creature&apos;s blood.  When this occurs, the vampire is effectively paralyzed as though staked through the heart.\n\n{i}Editor&apos;s Note: I find myself distrustful of this item.  Watering plants with vampire blood (a dangerous substance as readers of &quot;Guide to Vampire&quot; may recall) smacks entirely too much of the blackest necromancy.  --GWF{/i}\n\nUnless a blood seeker garlic clove is removed from the body of a paralyzed -or slain vampire, in 1d4 months it germinates as a lashweed (see Denizens of Darkness). Each clove of bloodseeker garlic is good for a single use.  Depending on the individual vampire, vampire blood can have a number of different effects. While the blood of some blood suckers is little different from  human blood, other vampires may have blood that is caustic, explosive, or hypnotic (other effects are entirely possible though). Caustic vampire blood does 1d6 damage on a direct hit and 1 point of splash damage. Explosive vampire blood does 1d3 damage to everything within a 3 foot blast radius when exposed to sunlight. Hypnotic blood causes those touched by it to be affected by the vampire&#145;s domination ability, as though the vampire had made a gaze attack. Vampire blood produces these effects so long as the vampire the blood was drawn from lives. Should a vampire be slain, there is a 50% chance that it&#146;s blood will become inert and turn putrid ( hypnotic vampire blood always turns putrid). Putrid vampire blood can not be used to create blood seeker garlic.\n\nCreating this item requires a powers check.\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 5th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Create Wondrous Item, {i}plant growth{/i}, three vials of vampire blood; {i}Market Price{/i}: 2,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: &#151;" compset="Wondrous" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="2000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLBoneJa" name="Bone of Jackals" description="Flavor Text:\nBrought to the Core by the {i}Casters of bones{/i}, this wooden replica of a femur is used to create wards against jackals.  The caster must speak the command word and hurl the {i}bone of jackals{/i} as far as they are able.  The bone creates a circle that  no jackal or jackal related creatures (such as werejackals) may enter.  The ward is  believed to last until the next setting or rising of the sun.  Should any intelligent being enter or leave the circle of protection the ward is dispelled.\n\nThe development of this particular item is a natural response on the part of the natives of the land beyond the Mists from which the {i}Casters of Bones{/i} hail.  The grasslands of that realm are said to be home to savage tribes of shapechanging jackals, similar to wolfweres, that roam the plains, living in hide tents and exhibiting a primitve culture with some parallels to that of the abber.\n{i}Editor&apos;s Note:  The Casters of Bones are an adventuring band noted for always leaving a spent bone of jackals at the site of their battles. --LWF{/i}\n\nA bone of jackals blocks jackal creatures with SR less than 16. The warded circle&#146;s radius is equal to the distance between the point from which the caster threw the bone and the point where the bone finally lands {the results of a Strength check x 5 feet}. Any jackal or related creature within the circle when it is created must make an SR check or be forced to flee from the warded area.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 7th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}magic circle against evil{/i}, a chip of jackal bone; {i}Market Price{/i}: 1,000 gp; 1 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="1000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLCtEEAm" name="Canjar Talisman, Evil Eye Amulet [INCOMPLETE]" description="SCRIPTING REQUIRED\n\nThe wearer of an evil eye amulet receives a +2 luck bonus to all Will saves against Enchantment spells. Those who seek to lay a curse against the wearer of an evil eye amulet find that the DC of the curse check is raised by +4. Each amulet has 50 charges before its magic is expired; amulets created for {i}giorgio{/i} [non-vistana], often carry a mere 5 charges, however.  These lesser amulets have a market price of 1,000 gp.  The Vistani can also craft curse cursed evil eye amulet that invoke penalties rather than bonuses.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 5th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}protection from curses{/i}, creator must be full-blooded Canjar; {i}Market Price{/i}: 10,000 gp." compset="Wondrous" summary="+2 luck bonus to Will saves vs Ench; +4 DC vs of any curses cast at wearer." stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="10000"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="50"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpNeck"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioCtMoonJe" name="Canjar Talisman, Moon Jewelry" description="REQUIRES SCRIPTING\n\nMoon jewelry provides the spellcaster who wears it with a luck modifier to her caster level checks (1d20 + caster level) to defeat an opponent&#146;s spell resistance. The  extent of the bonus is determined by thecurrent phase of the moon: +1 while the moon is waxing, rising to +2 during the full moon. However, the wearer suffers a -1 penalty to these checks when the moon is waning and &#151;2 during the new moon. Once the moon jewelry has modified a single caster level check, its magic remains in effect for an entire lunar cycle, even if the wearer removes the jewelry.\n\nThe moon must be visible when the moon jewelry is first used for it to take effect.\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 3rd; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, creator must be full-blooded Canjar; {i}Market Price{/i}: 2,700 gp." compset="Wondrous" summary="+x luck bonus/penalty to CL to overcome SR based on phase of moon." stacking="never">
    <comment><![CDATA[Is this something that can be added to any piece of jewelry or is it just an amulet?  Or did they give the amulet as an example?

For now, I'm leaving it just as an amulet.]]></comment>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="50"/>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="2700"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpNeck"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLCofPea" name="Coffer of Peace" description="Developed by halfling wizards in order to exterminate wights in the barrow country between Delagia and Tempe Falls in Darkon, this item in a stout iron coffer about a foot in length.  Within the coffer sits a crude effigy of a corpse, fashioned of rags, sticks and a small black stone.  To use this item, the halflings open the coffer and command an undead creature to return the grave.  This violently draws the undead&apos;s animating force (be it its soul or simply animating magic) into the effigy.\n\nCorporeal undead leave behind their empty shell, while incorporeal undead are drawn completely into the coffer.  The halfling then closes and locks the lid of the coffe, trapping the undead spirit inside.  The {i}coffer of peace{/i} must then be buried before the next rising or setting of the sun, destroying the spirit.\n\nUndead are allowed a Will save to escape the effects of a Coffer of peace. The coffer can contain a single undead spirit at a time.\nShould a coffer not be buried by the next rising or setting of the sun, the spirit within bursts free, returning to its body (if it had one). If the undead&#146;s body has been destroyed, the creature returns as a ghost (if it was intelligent; non-intelligent undead such as zombies simply cease to exist). This item does not affect darklords.\n\nCrafting this item requires a power check.\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 15th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}diminish undead{/i}, {i}trap the soul{/i}, an iron coffer; {i}Market Price{/i}: 3,250 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: 15 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="3250"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="15"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLCofEtR" name="Coffin of Eternal Rest" description="This item is a white sandalwood coffin with a gold trim and silk linin.  A gold holy symbol is worked into the center of the lid at chest height.  Any body placed in this coffin and properly interrred acts as though the spell {i}Eternal Slumber{/i} had been cast on it.  These items are popular with wealthy Darkonians, who import finely crafted castkets from Lamordia to be made into {i}coffins of eternal rest{/i}.\n\nThe body interred in a coffin of eternal rest automatically gains a Will save, with a +6 bonus, against any attempt to transform it into an undead creature.\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 13th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}etemal slumber{/i}, gold holy symbol; {i}Market Price{/i}: 8,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i} (empty): 100 lb." compset="Wondrous" summary="Bodies burried inside gain a +6 bon vs effects that would raise it as undead." stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="8000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="100"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLCryptL" name="Crypt Lock" description="This item is a chain of sturdy iron links witha compex silver-filigreed lock in the center.  When stretched across the entrance to a crypt, tomb, mausoleum, or other resting place of the dead, a {i}crypt lock{/i} snaps into place across the entrance, sealing it with an {i}arcane lock{/i} spell.  The crypt lock then places a {i}wall of stone{/i} over the entrance&apos;s inner face.  Finally, once the {i}crypt lock{/i} is in place, should anyone touch the door with the intend of opening it, the crypt lock delivers a {i}shocking grasp{/i} spell [CL14].\n\nWhich Hunters commonly use {i}crypt locks{/i} to seal undead in their tombs.  A {i}crypt lock{/i} seals only the entrance it is placed accross; crypts with multiple entrances require multiple locks to seal completely.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 14th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}guards and wards{/i}, an amazing lock, iron chain, silver holy symbol; {i}Market Price{/i}: 32,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: 3 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="32000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="3"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLEyeofW" name="Eye of the Wicked Sight [INCOMPETE]" description="SCRIPTING REQUIRED, add bootstrap for feat, add script to allow it to be worn with another eye slot item.\n\nAn eye-sized orb of black onyx, this item grants the user the ability to {i}see ethereal resonance{/i} (refer to {i}Barclay&apos;s Sight Unseen: The Theory of Ethereal Resonance{/i} for details).  When touched to the user&apos;s eye, {i}the eye of the wicked sight{/i} sinks into the socket, replacing the user&apos;s original eye.  The new eye is entirely a glossy black.\n\nThe eye oftlie wicked sight grants the user the {i}Ethereal Empathy{/i} feat. \nThis item also increases the user&apos;s OR [Outcast Rating] by +1 unless the affected eye is hidden (as by an eye-patch, for instance).\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 6th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous ltem, {i}see ethereal resonance{/i}, orb of black onyx; {i}Market Price{/i}: 3,600 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: &#151;" compset="Wondrous" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="3600"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpEyes"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLGloamC" name="Gloaming Candle" description="This item is a sickly green candle used in the detection of hags. When lit, the candle produces a greenish ?ame and copious amounts of foul-smelling smoke that drifts heavily and pools along the ground. The ?ame and smoke are detectable to most creatures, but hags cannot see or smell these effects, allowing hunters to easily determine whether an individual is a shape-changed hag. The wax of a gleaming candle contains a mixture of rare botanical ingredients, such as Lamordian {i}froid dulac{/i} toadstools, {i}green rancshure{/i} algae, and Hazlani {i}weeping reaper{/i} grain rust.\n\nThe smoke produced by this candle cannot be sensed by any practioners of witchcraft, including hags and hallowed witches (see chapter 5). Each gloaming candle burns for 5 hours. The candle may be snuffed and re-used later.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 7th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Create Wondrous item, {i}ground fog{/i}, {i}invisibility{/i}, {i}stinking cloud{/i}, 550 gp of rare herbs and fungi; {i}Market Price{/i}: 3,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: -" compset="Wondrous" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="3000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLHookTr" name="Hooka of Truth" description="Imported from Sri Raji, this enchanted water pipe of wine-colored glass produces clouds of smoke that act as a truth serum.  Forcing anyone within their radius to speak freely and truthfully.\n\n{i}Editor&#146;s Note: The Great Detective of Port-a-Lucine, Alanik Ray, received two of these devices in payment from a wealthy client of Rajian extraction.  One remains in Ray&#146;s possession, while the other was donated to the Guignol Museum at the University of Dementlieu.{/i}\n\nThe smoke of a {i}hookah of truth{/i} acts as a zone of truth spell. Those drawing from the hookah of truths two mouth pieces are immune to its effects. The immunity to the hookah&apos;s effects is limited to one person per mouthpiece; should two people try to share a mouthpiece, neither receives any immunity.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 15th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}zone of truth{/i}; {i}Market Price{/i}: 5,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: 10 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="5000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="10"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLLantJa" name="Lantern Jack" description="Dear Ladies, we think you&apos;ll find this item interesting; note the parallels with homunculi: Developed in Darkon with the aid of the late Professor Abelhous Nicholsi of the University of ll Aluk, {i}lantern jacks{/i} are small pumpkins that grow into servants on command. Initially, {i}lantem jacks{/i} appear to be fist&#151;sized pumpkins. In their fully grown form, {i}lantern jacks{/i} are jack&apos;o&#146; lantem-headed creatures which stand no more than three feet tall, with viney bodies and large leaves for hands and roots for feet. Each {i}lantern jack&#146;s{/i} head glows with an inner light of the brightness of a candle.\n\n{i}Lantern jacks{/i} are capable of using tools and weapons and always obey the orders of their animator.  They are mute but communicate via simple gestures.  {i}Lantern jacks{/i} exist for one week before their animating magic dissipates and they collapse into a pile of sickly-smelling decayed vegetable matter.\n\n{i}Lantern jacks{/i} have the same alignment as their animator.  {i}Lantern jacks{/i} must rest for three hours each night, plunging their root feet into the soil. The {i}lantern jack{/i} must make a Will save each night (DC = 10 + days of existence) or have its alignment move one step closer to neutral evil, having absorbed the taint of evil from the {i}Realm of Dread&#146;s{/i} soil. Once its alignment becomes neutral evil, the {i}lantern jack{/i} becomes free-willed and develops two overriding goals: to extend its existence beyond the end of its week and to murder its animator.\n\n[The monster for entry for a lantern jack has been added to Hero Labs]\nCR 1/6; Small plant; HD 1d8; 4 hp; lnit +1 (Dex); Spd 20ft.; AC14{+1 size, +1 Dex, +2 natural); Atk +1 melee (1d4, slam); SQ plant (Immune to mind-in?uencing effects, poison, sleep,  paralysis, stunning, and polymorphing. Not subject to critical hits.), low-light vision; AL. see above; SV Fort +1, Ref, +1, Will +0; Str 10, Dex 12, Con 10, Int 10, Wis 10, Cha 3.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 9th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, Knowiedge (nature), {i}awaken{/i}, a pumpkin; {i}Market Price{/i}: 9,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: 1 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="9000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="irRLRofRev" name="Ring of Reversion" description="From {i}Transpossession: A Guide to Phenomena{/i}, by Archmage Jacktin Tellurian: &#147;A simple rune-inscribed band of iron set with a blood red gamet, this ring forces the end of shapeshiftings and transpossession. When touched against a shapechanged creature or poli/morphed individual, the ring forces the target to revert back to its true, original form. However, for our purposes, this is the lesser of the ring&apos;s abilities.&quot;\n\n&quot;More pertinently, if the wearer touches the ring to a transpossessed creature, such as a victim of fiendish transposition or a {i}magic jar{/i} spell, the transpossessed minds are forced back into their original bodies. Interestingly, transpossessed individuals can feel the power of the ring. Individuals who wish to remain in the body they currently occupy feel this power as a sense of overwhelming dread emanating from the ring, while individuals who wish to escape their current body feel a sense of great hope when near the ring.&quot;\n\nTargets of either of a {i}ring of reversion{/i}&apos;s effects receive no saving throw.  The powers of a {i}ring of reversion{/i} can be used to counteract the effects of the {i}Apparatus{/i}. For a {i}ring of reversion{/i} to affect transpossessed minds, the minds&#146; original bodies must both be within 50 miles of the {i}ring of reversion{/i}.  Additionally, both bodies must still be intact for the reversion to occur.  The effects of {i}the ring of reversion{/i} cannot extend beyond the borders of the domain it is currently in.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 15th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Forge Ring, {i}remove curse{/i}; {i}Market Price{/i}: 30,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: &#151;" compset="Ring" summary="Reverses the affects of a Polymorph or Returns transposessed minds to original bodies.">
    <comment><![CDATA[This does not say weather or not it functions on curses that transform.  Or lycanthropy.  However, considering the spell used in its creation is "remove curse"  I'd have to say yes, but only for a short time refer to the spell "Shoulder Burden" or "Suppress Lycanthropy" for details on duration.]]></comment>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="30000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Ring"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLServCa" name="Servant Candle" description="On display in the central lobby of the Guignol Museum, and occasionally used by our faculty and staff, this thick, white, two-foot-tall candle silently floats after its master, helpfully providing any illumination needed. To activate a servant candle, the caster must speak the command word and toss the candle into the air. The candle ignites and begins floating at shoulder height two feet behind its master. The person who activated the servant candle becomes the candle&apos;s master for then on. Servant candles are able to follow simple instructions. A servant candle&apos;s flame does not consume wax, but can produce droplets of hot wax on command.\n\n{i}Editor&apos;s Note: My sister and I are aware of one Valachani witch of Hala, Sister Nimbus, who is noted for her collection of dozens of servant candles which follow her in a glowing halo on her travels throughout the Core.{/i} &#151;GWF\n\nServant Candle: A {i}servant candle{/i} can follow several simple instructions of one sentence in length (i.e. &#147;Go to the top of this bookcase&#148;), and its flame can not be put out by any means short of {i}dispel magic{/i}.  Unlike a {i}continual flame{/i}, the flame of a servant candle produces heat as well as light.  A servant candle that moves beyond 60 feet from its master becomes temporarily inert and gently snks to the ground.  However, once its master moves back in range, a simple command reactivates the servant candle.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 5th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}continual flame{/i}, {i}unseen servant{/i}, a large candle; {i}Market Price{/i}: 600 gp; {i}Weight{/i}; &#151;" compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="600"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLSSearM" name="Soul-Searcher Medallion" description="Sadly, the University does not actually own an example of this piece. Instead, we are providing this information from Prof. Agrippa&#146;s {i}Scrying and the Nature of Visions{/i} (please refer to the documents enclosed in the packet I&apos;ve included). This medallion is a small crystal orb that hangs from a silver chain. To use the {i}soul searcher medallion{/i}, the bearer must hold it in both hands and concentrate upon it. Initially, the bearer sees swirling motes of light within the crystal. The crystal then clears, after which the bearer may focus the crystal on any individual within 60 feet. The device reveals the true nature of the individual, exposing any curses, illusions, shapeshifting, magic dweomers, and so forth. {i}Soul seavcher medallions{/i} are notoriously fragile.  Records indicare that there are many cases where just when a {i}soul searcher medallion{/i} would have proven useful in a dire situation, the crystal shattered due to some chance misfortune.\n\nThe concentration time before the crystal clears is 1d4 rounds.\n\nThe medallion acts as a {i}true seeing spell{/i} (and additionally reveals any of the information listed in the item description above}. The {i}soul searcher medallion{/i} also reveals the true alignment of the individual, superceding Ravenloft&#146;s natural obscuring of moral alignments. The {i}soul searcher medallion{/i} does not make the examined individual&#146;s statistics apparent, nor does it supply information on the creature&#145;s attacks or possessions. A {i}soul searcher medallion{/i} has a hardness of 0 and can sustain only 1 point of damage before it shatters.\nWhenever a {i}soul searcher medallion{/i} or its bearer suffers a fall or any damage from a physical source (including force effects), the medallion must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC = 15 + damage taken) or be destroyed.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 11th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}true seeing{/i}, crystal orb, silver chain; {i}Market Price{/i}: 85,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: &#151;" compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="85000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="Hero" tag="EqpNeck"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder" name="Wondrous Item" abbrev="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLWichCo" name="Witch-Finder Compass" description="Kindly donated by your uncle George Weathermay, this item is a wood and glass compass one foot in diameter. Within its dome, an iron needle floats in holy water.  Instead of pointing north, the needle within points toward the nearest witch.  Many witch-hunters use {i}witch-finder compasses{/i} to hunt hags and wicked sorceresses.\n\n{i}Editor&#146;s Note: We asked Uncle George about this item while preparing the first chapter of this text. He indicated that he was able to use this device to great effect while hunting hag; in Nova Vaasa, including the green hagSemine. When the University of Dementlieu contacted him about acquiring some of the equipment he used in hunting creatures of the night, Uncle George passed them the older and less reliable of the two witch-finder compasses he had acquired.{/i}&#151;GWF\n\nWitch-finder compasses point to the nearest female witchcraft-using spellcaster, including hags and witches of Hala.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 16th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Create Wondrous Item, {i}discern location{/i}; {i}Market Price{/i}: 1,300 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: 5 lb." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="1300"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="5"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder" name="Wondrous Item" abbrev="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLWolfPa" name="Wolfspaw" description="This powerful item is the leathery paw of a wolf, stuffed with belladonna and rare herbs before being sewn shut.  It can be worn around the neck on a leather strap.  No lupine creatures, including wolves, worgs, shapechangers or undead in wolf or hybrid form can approach the bearer of this talisman. The protection fails if the paw&#146;s bearer tries toforce the barrier against a blocked creature.\n\nNo creatures in lupine forrn with SR less than 16 can cross the boundary of a 10-foot-radius circle centered on the paw.  Nor can such creatures cannot voluntarily transform into any wolf-like form (regardless of the method used to do so) while within the aura&apos;s radius.  A creature that involuntarily assumes a iupine form while within the wolfspaw&apos;s radius (such as an afflicted werewolf exposed to its trigger) must flee the area of effect on its next available action.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 5th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}magic circle against evil{/i}, heart&#146;s blood of a dire wolf; {i}Market Price{/i}: 30,000 gp." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="30000"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder" name="Wondrous Item" abbrev="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLBedofM" name="Bed of Meditation" description="This bed of nails is of Sri Rajian origin. ln the Verdutous Lands, monks, swamis, and fakits use it to hone their mental abilities. Apparently, by attempting to transcend the discomfort of sitting or lying on the bed of nails, users undergo a mystical realignment of their {i}chakras{/i}: points through which the body&#146;s life energy flows. This realignment brings about an increase in the user&apos;s mental prowess and sagacity.  Tales in Sri Raji speak of venerable gurus who attained transcendent enlightenment through the use of the bed of meditation and escaped the physical world.\n\nFor each hour a user sits or lies on the {i}bed of meditation{/i}, she suffers 1d4-2 points of damage and gains an effective +1 bonus to her Wisdom and lntelligence scores (to a maximum bonus of +10 each). The effective bonus disappears entirely one hour after the user leaves the bed of nails.  Beds of meditation can be used only by monks and divine spellcasters.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 10th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}zone of truth{/i}; {i}Market Price{/i}: 90,000 gp; {i}Weighs{/i}: 50 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="90000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="50"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="AlwaysAvl"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLCenWar" name="Censer of Warding" description="The Cult of the Morninglord first created these silver censers to ward their holy places against vampires and other creatures of the night.  Over the years, other religions have learned the art of crafting these objects.  {i}Censers of warding{/i} are silver and intricately decorated with symbols of the deities of various religions, such as the Mominglord, Ezra, or Hala, and each hangs by silver chains from a silver-trimmed rod of oak.  To protect a building, the censer of warding must be filled with holy incense and, as the incense burns, the caster must walk the full outer perimeter of the building, chanting orisons and singing hymns to a god of light.  Once this is done, the building is warded against all undead until the following dawn. Should any undead be within the structure when the censer of warding is used, the ward does not work.\n\nA {i}censer of warding{/i} blocks undead with SR less than 16 from entering a structure.  Darklords are immune to the effects of this item.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 8th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}consecrate{/i}; {i}Market Price{/i}: 50,000 gp; {i}Weighs{/i} 3 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="50000"/>
    <fieldval field="gWeight" value="3"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLIcEtOr" name="Icon of the Eternal Order" description="Based in the folklore of the Darkonians, the Eternal Order&apos;s traditions boast an array of grim heroes who strove to hold the Gray Realm in check. These {i}mortisants{/i} are commemorated in ornately framed religious paintings called icons.\n\nPopular images of icons include Darkon&#146;s great legendary hero Nirdeth; Anamnesis, the first Undertaker of Darkon; and Sarilas, who sacrificed herself to destroy the crypts of Dimgnos. Through complex ritual, the Etemal Order imbues certain icons with the ability to draw the spirits of {i}mortisants{/i} from the Gray Realm to advise and heal supplicanrs who pray beneath the icon&apos;s gaze, icons of the Eternal Order can produce a {i}divination{/i} spell once per day and a {i}cure light wounds{/i} spell twice per day.  Each icon mentally speaks to supplicants in the voice of the {i}mortisants{/i} it depicts.\n\n{i}Caster Level{/i}: 9th; {i}Prerequisites{/i}: Create Wondrous Item, Craft (painting), {i}cure moderate wounds{/i}, {i}divination{/i}; {i}Market Price{/i}: 54,000 gp; {i}Weight{/i}: 3 lb." compset="Wondrous" stacking="never">
