  <thing id="iRLBloodkn" name="Bloodknife [Artifact]" description="NEEDS SPECIAL and Bootstrap script for Diamond of the Sun.\nNEEDS Special for Good/Evil Wielder Script and Wolf Companion.\n\n&#147;The one who was orphaned shall return during the night of greatest darkness with the bane of  the evil one. With the wolf spirit, the one shall claim the birthright of the sun, and the evil one&apos;s shadow will be cleansed from the land. Blood shall turn to water, and shadow tum to light; all will be restored. and day will burn the night.&quot; {i}&#151;Ancient Tales of the Vistani{/i}, author unknown.  The prophecy recorded above is part of the lore relating to an artifact called the {i}Bloodknife{/i}, also known to vampires as the {i}Bane of the Ancients{/i}.\n\nTreasure hunters throughout the Land of Mists have searched for this dagger for nearly two centuries.  The {i}Bloodknife{/i} is a large dagger with a foot-long blade, and the whole of the weapon, hilt and blade, is crafted from a single huge ruby. Embedded in the hilt are two small cameos, one depicting a wolf with open jaws howling at the moon, and the other depicting an aristocratic, mustached man whose mouth is filled with fangs. The wolf cameo has an indentation where a small jewel referred to as the {i}&#147;Diamond of the Sun&quot;{/i} is supposed to be fitted. The {i}Diamond ofthe Sun{/i} was supposedly a small diamond with gold veins that magnified the powers of the {i}Bloodknife{/i}, but its current fate remains a mystery.\n\nBeyond the basic facts of the item itself, the history and purpose of the {i}Bloodknife{/i} are unclear.  Wild tales of ancient royal bloodlines, Vistani kingdoms, reincamation, lycanthropy, vampire warlords, and sundry other fairy-tale embellishments make an accurate reading of the {i}Bloodknife{/i}&apos;s true past extremely difficult.  Thus, research into the {i}Bloodknife{/i} has been relegated to a position of low priority for our scholars.\n\nThe {i}Bloodknife{/i} is a +2 dagger that glows with ruddy light.  The dagger&apos;s glow intensifies in the presence of vampires, becoming equal to that of a torch.  In addition, the {i}Bloodknife{/i} tingles and emits a throbbing hum when within 500 feet of a vampire.  By watching the intensity of these effects, the {i}Bloodknife&apos;s{/i} owner can detect the location and proximity of these bloodsuckers In the hands of a character of good alignment, the {i}Bloodknife{/i} drains the negative energy of any vampire or vampire spawn on a successful hit, instantly destroying the creature.  The target can make a Will save (DC 25) to negate this effect.  True vampires gain a +1 profane bonus to this saving throw for each century of undeath.  Thus, a 500-year-old vampire makes the Will save with a +5 bonus. Vampire spawn do not gain this benefit.  If a vampire successfully saves against the energy-draining effects of the {i}Bloodknife{/i}, it is immune to the {i}Bloodknife{/i}&apos;s energy drain from that point on.  When a character of good alignment takes possession of the {i}Bloodknife{/i}, the dagger {i}awakens{/i} the nearest wolf (as per the spell) and grants it a telepathic rapport with the knife&apos;s owner.  The wolf then seeks out the owner and joins her as an animal companion.  The wolf companion granted by the knife is {b}{u}not{/u}{/b} a dread companion, and has the alignment of the knife&#146;s new owner.\n\nIn the hands of an evil-aligned wielder, the {i}Bloodknife{/i} drains the souls of the living on a successful hit.  Living victims can attempt a Fortitude save (DC 25) to negate this effect.  The wielder of the {i}Bloodknife{/i} may choose to absorb part of the souls claimed by the weapon, adding an effective +1 extra hit point to her total for every 2 Hit Dice possessed by the creature slain.  Thus, if an evil wielder slays a living creature with 7 HD, she can add +3 hit points to her total.\n\nThe owner keeps this effective bonus to her hit points for as long as she retains physical possession of the {i}Bloodknife.{/i}  Using the {i}Bloodknife{/i} in this manner requires a powers check.\n\nIf the {i}Diamond of the Sun{/i} is found and placed in its setting, then three times pet day the wielder of the {i}Bloodknife{/i} can produce a {i}sunburst{/i} as the spell cast by a 20th-level caster.  The {i}sunburst{/i} is always centered on the {i}Bloodknife{/i}.\n\nThe {i}Bloodknife{/i} was specifically created to find the true heirs to the throne of an obscure domain, conquered long ago by a cruel and despotic vampire lord known as Velkaarn, and to aid them in his destruction.  The {i}Bloodknife{/i} acts as a death bane weapon against this foul being.\n\nUnfortunately, the princes of that land are long dead, the blade&#146;s task unfinished.  Because of this failure, their souls are trapped in the Realm of Dread, rebom time and again, until the day Velkaarn is slain.  The {i}Bloodknife{/i} gravitates toward the reincarnated souls of its true masters, slowly working its way closer to its target over time.  The {i}Bloodknife{/i} gravitates toward human or half-Vistani player characters with the {i}Reincanated{/i} feat, as well those with the {i}Lunatic{/i} feat." compset="MagicWep" uniqueness="useronce">
