    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLCatFel" name="Cat of Felkovic" description="According to reports circulating throughout the southeastern countries. this artifact is a one-inch-tall jade statuette in the shape of a house cat.\n\nThe cat wears a contented expression and sits on a circular base, which bears a command word along the edge. When the statuette is tossed to the  ground and the command word spoken, the {i}Cat of Felkovic{/i} transforms, like a figurine of wondrous power, into a massive great cat with incisors the length of a man&apos;s forearm. This cat obeys whoever speaks the command word to bring it forth.  The cat is harmless so long as it is fed once each day.  If the cat is recalled while it is eating, its kill becomes part of the statue, appearing in miniature beneath the cat&#146;s jade forepaws.\n\nAccording to reports, the {i}Cat of Felkovic{/i} is intimately linked to Baron Urik von Kharkov of Valachan.  Apparently, the {i}Cat of Felkovic{/i} attacked Baron von Kharkov shortly after he inherited the baronial title from his late father.\n\n{i}Editors Note: By some accounts, Felkovic was a mage who had been in love with one of the baron&apos;s many doomed brides, and he somehow crafted the cat to seek revenge. He does not seem to have survived to put his creation to use, however.{/i}&#151;GWF\n\nEach day the cat is not fed by its owner, it animates on its own during the night and hunts for meat.  The first night, the {i}Cat of Felkovic{/i} merely animates in the form of a common house cat.  Each subsequent night, the cat awakens as a progressively larger, fiercer cat.\n\nThe cat hunts and kills the most convenient prey appropriate to its current size, starting with birds and mice as a house cat and working up to human prey, such as its owner, as a dire tiger.  When animated by hunger, the {i}Cat of Felkovic{/i} cannot be controlled by its owner.  When the cat has eaten its fill, it returns to where it animated and reverts to figurine form.\n\nIn addition to the statistics and abilities of each form it takes, the {i}Cat of Felkovic{/i} is immune to all spell and spell-like effects and has damage reduction 30/+2.  lf the cat is &quot;slain,&quot; it reverts to figurine form until the next night it needs to feed.\nThe {i}Cat of Felkovic{/i} is one of the few objects that can permanently slay Baron Urik von Kharkov.  Should the cat slay the baron, it reverts to figurine form, never to animate again.\n{align left}\nTable 3-1: {i}The Cat of Felkovic{/i}\n|      Cat      Days Without      Hit        Meat   CR\n|    Type         Feeding          Dice       Req&apos;d\n| House cat         1             1/2d8      1 lb.      1\n| Leopard            2              3d8      20 lbs      3\n| Plains cat         3           4d8+12   30 lbs.     4\n| Lion                  4           5d8+10   40 lbs.    4\n| Tiger                 5           6d8+18   50 lbs.    5\n| Dire lion            6           8d8+24   60 lbs.    6\n| Dire tiger           7         16d8+48   70 lbs.    9" compset="Wondrous" uniqueness="useronce">
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder" name="Wondrous Item" abbrev="Wonder"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="iRLRavanaB" name="Ravana&apos;s Bane [Artifact]" description="While many details of this account strain credibility, you may find this excerpt from an interview with Sri Rajian sorcerer and explorer Soma Purusha to be of interest:\n\nDr. Noge Spengler: Can you tell me about the item in this drawing? (Indicates a stylized ink drawing of an omate arrow or bolt)\n\nSoma Punishaz Yes, of course. This is a sketch of {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i}, a legendary weapon in the lore of my land. lt is supposedly a crossbow bolt of great mystic power.\n\nSpengler: Can you elaborate on the back- ground of this piece for me?\n\nPurusha: According to the tale, the Maharaja Arijani, in days long past, fought a terrible war to rid to world of the demons known in our land as {i}rakshasa{/i}. So great and terrible was the wrath he poured upon the tiger-demons that the god of the {i}rakshasa{/i}, Ravana, come to earth in living form to plead for Arijani to have mercy on his people.\n\nSpengler: And what did Maharaja Arijani do?\n\nPurusha: Arijani stole the secret of the tiger-demons so that they could lay neither claw nor fang upon him.  He then used the sacred bolt {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} and shot Ravana in the heart, slaying the {i}rakshasa{/i} god instantly.\n\nSpengler: Most interesting. What of {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} today!\n\nPurusha: The bolt absorbed the taint of the god of the tiger demons, becoming the only artifact of the {i}rakshasa{/i} that could touch Maharaja Arijani. For a long time {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} was lost.  Recently, it was found cast into the form ofa statue, but it was restored to its true form by an artisan in Tvashti. I know not where it passed from there, but the power of {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} undoubtedly still lurks in this world, hungry for the soul of Arijani.\n\nThis silver crossbow bolt was used by the darklord ofSri Raji, the {i}rakshasa{/i} Arijani, to slay the avatar of his father, Ravana, god of the rakshasa. {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} acts as a +1 silver crossbow bolt. However, should it be used against Arijani, {i}Ranvana&apos;s Bane{/i} instantly slays the darklord with a successful attack. After slaying Arijani, {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} will melt into a pile of twisted slag; this is the only known means of destroying this artifact.\nPossessing {i}Ravana&#146;s Bane{/i} is hazardous, for this weapon opens its owner to the will of Ravana.  Anyone who owns {i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} for one month draws the attention of Ravana&apos;s minions, who will attempt to enter the Realm of Dread via transposition with the owner. Once the transposition is complete, the owner of {i}Ravana&#146;s Bane{/i} will have been replaced by a {i}rakshasa{/i}, who attempts to seek out and slay Arijani.\n{i}Ravana&apos;s Bane{/i} is currently hidden deep in the jungles of Sri Raji. The bolt lies on an altar in a crumbling temple of the destroyer god, Shiva, where monks guard the artifact from the unenlightened." compset="MagicWep" uniqueness="useronce">
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="1"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <tag group="IsWeapon" tag="wBolts"/>
    <tag group="IsWeapon" tag="wDagger"/>
    <child entity="wSpecMagic">
      <bootstrap thing="wBolts"></bootstrap>
      </child>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gRLAnesth" name="Anesthetic" description="The Flesh of a creature that swallows or is injected with anesthetic is numbed to all physical pain.  This is most useful in easing the suffering of a badly wounded comrade.  I have heard some accounts of folk who imbibe anesthetic {i}before{/i} entering combat, using it as a preventative measure to block the pain of any wounds they might suffer.  This practice is unwise, however.  We feel pain for a reason; deny the wamings sent by your Flesh at your peril.\n\nMarket Price: 50 gp.\n\nDC 25. This substance works like a crude version of the {i}anesthesia{/i} spell.  A creature that ingests anesthetic must make a successful Fortitude save (DC 15) or lose all physical sensation.  The creature ignores half of all subdual damage it suffers and gains a +4 circumstance bonus to Fortitude saves against stun effects (such as a monk&apos;s stunning attack).  The creature also suffers an effective -4 Dexterity decrease. If the creature is a player character, the player should not be told how many hit points the character has remaining.  Anesthetic cannot affect creatures immune to poison.  The effects of one dose of anesthetic wear off after five minutes; multiple doses extend the duration but do not stack.\n\nA person may create Anesthetic with a DC 25 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge." compset="Gear" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="50"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="OilPotion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearNoSize"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gRLCataPoi" name="Catalytic Poison" description="While I admit these substances may have nefarious uses, {i}catalytic poisons{/i} can also be invaluable when a small sample of tissue (such as a tuft of hair or a few drops of fresh blood) is all an investigator has to link a creature to its crimes.  The alchemist uses the tissue sample to create a catalytic solution that is then blended with a dose of poison (including harmless chemicals such as {i}anesthetic{/i}). The catalyst alters the properties of the poison, binding it to the signature of the tissue sample.  The resulting {i}catalytic poison{/i} is rendered inert to all but the individual creature that supplied the sample &#151; most useful in narrowing a list of suspects.\n\nHowever, I should note my suspicions that a {i}catalytic poison{/i} may not be able to distinguish between creatures that are physically identical, such as arcane clones &#151; or even twin sisters such as yourselves.\n\nMarket Price: 30 gp plus cost of poison.\nCatalytic Poison: DC 25\n\nA person may create a {i}Catalytic Poison{/i} with a DC 25 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge." compset="Gear" summary="Creates a poison keyed to a specific target, DC is always 25." stacking="merge">
    <comment>Is there a way to link this to other poisons?</comment>
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="30"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearNoSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="CustomSpec"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Poisons"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gRLDisapIn" name="Disappearing Ink" description="This ink appears black in its vial and while used in writing, but fades to perfect transparency a few minutes after exposure to air.  The listed market price includes an equivalent amount of restorative, a clear liquid which, brushed over the vanished writing, permanently restores it to its original color.  While useful for the usual purpose of sending secret messages, l believe it may also be useful against shapechanging foes such as doppelgangers.  The ink is not water-soluble and can be washed off only with judicious soap and scrubbing.  lf splashed on a creature in one form, the ink quickly fades and may leave the foe unaware that it has been marked. Regardless of the form it takes later, the ink remains on its skin, immediately revealed by an application of the restorative.\nMarket Price: 5 gp per ounce.\n\nDisappearing Ink: DC 20. Writing vanishes 1d4 minutes after exposure to air. Contact with the restorative makes ink reappear in 1 round.\n\nA person may create a {i}Disappearing Ink{/i} with a DC 20 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge." compset="Gear" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="5"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearNoSize"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="OilPotion"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gRLEther" name="Ether" description="This pungent liquid is often known as &#147;sweet vitriol&quot; in alchemical circles. As with several other substances listed here, ether must be kept in an airtight container; it rapidly vaporizes when in contact with air, and inhaling its sulfuric vapors dulls the senses. If inhaled for too long or too deeply, a subject may even rapidly enter a dream-like fugue or fall unconscious. If held over a subject&#146;s face, an ether-soaked cloth can quickly render a foe unconscious while inflicting no pain or lasting harm. A single bottle of ether is good for six such applications; each dose remains potent for one minute after being exposed to air.\nMarket Price: 50 gp.\n\nDC 25. Ether is a non-lethal, inhaled poison: Fortitude save (DC 15); initial damage 3d6 points of subdual damage, secondary damage none.\nHolding an ether rag over the face of a resisting foe requires a successful grapple check. The foe must make a Fortitude save each round an ether rag is held over its face.\n\nA person may create 1 bottle of {i}Ether{/i} with a DC 25 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge." compset="Gear" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="50"/>
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="6"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Poisons"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearNoSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gRLGlowJar" name="Glow Jar" description="Chymists usually sell this concoction in small, sealed glass jars.  Violently shaking the jar causes a chemical reaction, and the fluid within begins to glow with a gentle, silvery-blue luminescence, not unlike the light of a firefly. A glow jar casts light as brightly as a candle, but does not require air and sheds neither heat nor flame.\n\nDC 25. Illuminates a 5-foot radius with the brightness of a candle for one hour.\n\nA person may create 1 {i}Glow Jar{/i} with a DC 25 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge." compset="Gear" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="20"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="SpecSubs"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearNoSize"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gRLHeatPou" name="Heat Pouch" description="This granular substance is usually poured into a small cloth sack, which is then sewn shut.  It shares a few ingredients with alchemist&#146;s fire.  If the heat pouch is violently shaken or crushed, the substance reacts, shedding a considerable degree of warmth for about six hours.  If worn against the skin, a heat pouch offers its bearer a small degree of protection against extremely cold temperatures. The pouch is also warm enough to fool the senses of some creatures that may be drawn to body heat, such as the vile vermin known as carrion stalkers.\nMarket Price: 15 gp.\n\nDC 20. Grants its bearer cold resistance 2 vs. subdual damage dealt by cold temperatures for six hours. (See &#147;Cold Dangers&quot; in chapter 3 of the {i}Dungeon Master&apos;s Guide{/i}.)\n\nA person may create 1 {i}Heat Pouch{/i} with a DC 20 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge." compset="Gear" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="15"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="AdventGear"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearNoSize"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="gRLHerbSol" name="Herbal Solution" description="An alchemist creates this simple solution by suspending trace amounts of a chosen herb in a watery fluid.  While harmless to most creatures, contact with an herbal solution bums the skin of any creature that suffers a harmful allergen to the chosen herb, such as werewolves to wolfsbane [belladonna berries].  If exposed, the creature&#146;s skin immediately develops painful welts.\nMarket Price: 10 gp plus cost of herbs.\n\nDC 20. Striking a foe with a flask of herbal solution is a ranged touch attack that does not provoke attacks of opportunity. Contact with an herbal solution damages creatures that have the selected herb as a harmful allergen. Such a creature must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC 15) or suffer 2d4 points of damage on a direct strike or 1 point if splashed.\n\nPhenotype         Chemical Aversion (Allergens)\nVampire              Garlic\nWerebear          Belladonna\nWereboar          Camphor\nWerejackal        Fennel\nWerejaguar       Cocoa\nWereleopard     Mercury\nWererat             Varies\nWereraven        Unknown\nWereray             Water Lily\nWeretiger          Ginseng\nWerewolf           Wolfsbane\n\nA person may create 1 flask of an {i}Herbal Solution{/i} with a DC 20 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge." compset="Gear" stacking="merge">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="10"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Poisons"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="GearNoSize"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="CustomSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ioRLNighDr" name="Night Drops" description="The user must dribble a bit of this clear solution into each eye for it to take effect.  Once done, the drops dilate the pupils to an extreme degree, rendering the user&apos;s eyes highly sensitive to light.  This can be quite useful in situations where investigators must work under cover of darkness, but it does require forethought; sudden exposure to bright light can all but blind the user. While night drops may be of little use to elves, dwarves and similar beasts, it can aid those of us whose vision is not so keen.\nMarker Price: 30 gp.\n\nDC 25. For one hour, the user gains low-light vision (see the {i}Player&apos;s Handbook{/i}) and light sensitivity, suffering a -1 penalty to all attack rolls in bright sunlight or within the radius of a daylight spell.\n\nA person may create 1 bottle of {i}Night Drops{/i} with a DC 25 Profession (Alchemy) check, provided they have access to Cultural Level 4 (Classical) knowledge.\n\n{b}Note:{/b} Using this in Hero Labs, equip this and it will apply the bonuses to your character." compset="Wondrous">
    <fieldval field="gCost" value="30"/>
    <usesource source="VRArsen"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="EquipMag"/>
    <tag group="gType" tag="Wonder"/>
