  <thing id="xAlcChLLik" name="Lifelike" description="The creation of an alchemical child is such a sophisticated process that the resulting creature mimics a living biology in many ways.  The child can eat, drink, breathe and sleep, though it does not truly need to do any of this. The child even ages nonnally for a member of the base creature&#146;s race and bleeds if cut, though the fluid is more akin to quintessence than true blood.  Lifelike constructs are not immune to bleeding effects or subdual damage, and they die at -10 hit points (rather than at 0 hp), like a living creature.  An alchemical child is considered a living creature in respect to the effects of alchemical formulae." compset="Special">
