  <thing id="fRLRefinem" name="Refinements" description="{align left}\nAn enlightened child may select up to three &quot;refinements&quot; from the following list to bestow on her creation.  The alchemist must add a special ingredient to the concoction to bestow each refinement.\n\n{i}Acidic{/i} (Ex): At will, the child can alter its body chemistry to render its touch highly corrosive.  This adds +1d6 points of acid damage to any attacks the child makes with its natural weapons,  including unarmed strikes.  Opponents grappling with the child and any items wom by the child automatically suffer the damage each round they maintain contact.  {i}Ingredient:{/i} A flask of acid.\n\n{i}Fluid{/i} (Ex): At will, the child can partially liquefy its body and flow around different objects like water. It can fit through any non-watertight crack or opening. The child can liquefy or solidify as a full-round action.  {i}Ingredient:{/i} A sample taken from any ooze.\n\n{i}Hemetic{/i} (Ex): The child&apos;s flesh automatically cally seals allopen wounds.  It is immune to bleeding effects (such as those caused by a weapon of wounding), and it can reattach a severed limb instantly by holding it to the stump.  Severed limbs dissolve if not reattached within one minute, however.  {i}Ingredient:{/i} A pint of troll&apos;s blood.\n\n{i}Idealized{/i} (Ex): The child does not age and is immune to aging effects.  {i}Ingredient:{/i} A pint of blood taken from any fey creature.\n\n{i}Malleable{/i} (Ex): The child possesses a limited ability to reshape its features, mimicking other individuals of the same race of its base creature as effectively as a user of the {i}alter self{/i} spell.  The child can stay in these alternate forms indefinitely, and can assume a new form or revert to its true form as a standard action.  lf a malleable child is slain, it briefly reverts to its true form before dissolving.  {i}Ingredients:{/i} A pint of doppelganger blood and small tissue sample taken from each individual to be mimicked.\n\n{i}Toxic{/i} (Ex): The child&apos;s blood is poisonous: lngested, Fortitude save (DC 10 + 1/2 child&#146;s HD), initial damage 1 temporary Constitution, secondary damage 1d8 temporary Constitution. This damage applies to any creature that damages the child with a bite attack. The child can also drain its own blood to prepare one application of the toxin, suffering 1 point of damage per Hit Die in the process. {i}lngledient:{/i} A vial of arsenic (120 gp)." compset="Feat" summary="Select the number of refinements your alchemical child has.">
    <comment>thingid.kKnowNoble|thingid.kKnowRel</comment>
    <fieldval field="ftCandExpr" value="thingid.xRLNoRefin|thingid.xRLOnRefin|thingid.xRLTwRefin|thingid.xRLThRefin"/>
    <usesource source="KniAnsalon" parent="pDL" name="Knightly Orders of Ansalon"/>
